SECTION 10 — OPEN SOURCE COMPONENTS

The seng programming language is an original work created independently by
NoCorps.org build by KANAGARAJ-M. The Software is written in the C programming language and does
not incorporate any third-party open-source libraries or components at
runtime. The Software depends only on standard C library functions (libc)
and the standard math library (libm), both of which are universally
available on all supported platforms. The seng installer may optionally
download or reference the GCC compiler (GNU Compiler Collection) and/or
Clang LLVM compiler, which are separate open-source projects governed by
their own respective licenses (GPLv3 and Apache 2.0 respectively) and are
not part of this Software.

SECTION 11 — PLATFORM SUPPORT

