SECTION 15 — PRIVACY POLICY

The seng programming language software, including its compiled installer, does
not collect, transmit, or share any personal data, usage statistics, telemetry
information, or identifying information from your computer or system. The
Software operates entirely offline. No analytics, tracking scripts, or network
requests are made during normal operation. Any internet connectivity used by
the installer is solely for downloading optional dependencies (such as GCC)
from their official distribution servers, and no information about the user
or their system is transmitted to NoCorps.org build by KANAGARAJ-M or any third party during this
process. For full privacy information, visit nocorps.org/privacy.

SECTION 16 — CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

The seng programming language is designed to be accessible to learners of
all ages, including students and young learners who are new to programming.
The Software does not collect any personal information from users of any age.
Parents and guardians are encouraged to supervise the use of any software
by minors. The Software itself presents no privacy risks, as it performs
no data collection or transmission. The official website at nocorps.org
complies with applicable children's privacy protection laws and regulations
where required.

SECTION 17 — ACCESSIBILITY

NoCorps.org build by KANAGARAJ-M is committed to making the seng programming language accessible
to users of all abilities and technical backgrounds. The language's core design
philosophy of using plain English syntax is intended to lower the barrier
to entry for programming education. The Software is provided in a format
compatible with screen readers and accessibility tools where technically
feasible. If you encounter accessibility barriers in the Software or its
documentation, please contact us at nocorps.org to report the issue.
We will make reasonable efforts to address documented accessibility concerns
in future releases.

